---
title: Mushroom & Tomato Tortelloni Topped with Italian Cheese Blend & Fresh Parsley
description: This delicious bowl of pasta is the total package! Our chefs paired these comforting cheese-stuffed pasta with mushrooms and tossed it all together in a rich tomato sauce to deliver an extra-tender bite and a huge amount of flavor. Shower your tortelloni with a melty Italian cheese blend and fresh parsley before serving for the perfect weeknight dinner idea—ready to enjoy in just 15 minutes.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/15-minute-mushroom-and-tomato-tortelloni-866d23fd.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/mushroom-tomato-tortelloni-63bd89ef978582d39f0f108c-9dfbf185.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/mushroom-tomato-tortelloni-63bd89ef978582d39f0f108c
course: main course
author: Sara Heilman
nutrition:
  calories: 610 kcal
  fat: 22 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 78 g
  sugar: 21 g
  protein: 27 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 1330 mg
time required: 15 minutes
cuisine: Italian
servings: 2
---

Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @yellow onion{1} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and roughly chop @button mushrooms{4%ounce}. Roughly chop @parsley{¼%ounce}.

Once boiling, add @tortelloni{9%ounce} to #pot. Reduce to a low simmer and cook until tender and floating to the top, ~{3-4%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water (1 cup for 4 servings), then drain.

While tortelloni cooks, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and mushrooms; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until onions are slightly translucent, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, half the @fry seasoning{1%tbsp}, half the @chili flakes{1%tsp}, ½ tsp @italian seasoning{1%tbsp}, and a pinch of @sugar{}. (For 4 servings, use all the Fry Seasoning, all the chili flakes, and 1 tsp Italian Seasoning.) Reduce heat to medium; simmer, stirring occasionally, until slightly reduced and thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from heat.

Stir drained tortelloni and half the @italian cheese blend{½%cup} into pan with sauce. (TIP: If your pan isn't large enough, transfer sauce to #pot{} used to cook tortelloni. If needed, stir in reserved cooking water a splash at a time until tortelloni are thoroughly coated in sauce.) Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide pasta between bowls. Top with remaining italian cheese blend and garnish with parsley. Serve.

> This delicious bowl of pasta is the total package! Shower your tortelloni with a melty Italian cheese blend and fresh parsley before serving for the perfect weeknight dinner idea—ready to enjoy in just 15 minutes.